		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Midscanline CHR bank switch demo</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My good old mid-scanline demo from 2009 uploaded again.<br /><br />It shows how to change CHR-ROM banks mid-scanline to bypass the 256-tiles limitation. In this example it alternate between the playfield CHR bank and the letter's CHR bank, simulating what the MMC4 does by hardware in Fire Emblem.<br /><br />I added a second variant of it which changes the low 3 bit of the scrolling by writes to $2005.1<br />It's less impressive though.<br /><br />Comes with NTSC and PAL variants, all tested on hardware (powerpak).

		
